OL,3,C'Welcome to hell': Dangerous cladding
OL,4,Chas left families trapped or homeless
OL,6,FOfficial figures reveal more than a
OL,7,Fthird of high rise buildings in
OL,8,FGreater Manchester have been
OL,9,Fidentified as having serious fire
OL,10,Fsafety faults since 2017. Of those,
OL,11,FITV News has learnt, nearly 200
OL,12,Fbuildings are so dangerous, special
OL,13,Femergency measures, such as round the
OL,14,Fclock fire patrols are in place
OL,15,Findefinitely to keep residents safe.
OL,17,FLocal leaders have blamed delays in
OL,18,Fgovernment funding and developers
OL,19,Frefusing to pay for the slow progress.
OL,20,FThis is a scenario being repeated in
OL,21,Ftowns and cities across the UK.
