OL,3,C'Welcome to hell': Dangerous cladding
OL,4,Chas left families trapped or homeless
OL,6,FAs a leaseholder Ms Malik is still
OL,7,Freceiving bills for the annual service
OL,8,Fcharge and management fees to the tune
OL,9,Fof #4000 a year, even though she
OL,10,Fhasn't lived there for four years.
OL,12,F"I'm still being billed for window
OL,13,Fcleaning, security, CCTV, and no
OL,14,Fnothing is happening here. The only
OL,15,Fresidents. are the pigeons," she said.
OL,17,FMs Malik is among the estimated 16,000
OL,18,Fresidents in high and mid-rise blocks
OL,19,Fthat have been forced to leave homes
OL,20,Fdue to a fire or fire safety defects
OL,21,Fsince 2017.
