OL,3,C'Welcome to hell': Dangerous cladding
OL,4,Chas left families trapped or homeless
OL,6,FNew analysis for ITV news by campaign
OL,7,Fgroup End Our Cladding Scandal shows
OL,8,Fthat in the last three months alone,
OL,9,F600 people have had to leave their
OL,10,Fhomes.
OL,12,FMs Malik has been left effectively
OL,13,Fhomeless and she now lives in a
OL,14,Fstudent hostel with no carpet, a
OL,15,Fbucket to wash laundry and a bathroom
OL,16,Fshared with 20 other people.
OL,18,F"For me it's like I am living in a
OL,19,Fcave, without light, without any hope.
OL,20,FEvery day I cry," she said.
